headline: Why Dollar General Stock Tumbled on Tuesday
summary: A recommendation downgrade from a veteran investment bank had a predictable effect on Dollar General (NYSE: DG) stock Tuesday.  The institution behind the move was Goldman Sachs, whose analyst Kate McShane lowered her rating on Dollar General to neutral -- at a price target of $116 per share -- from her preceding buy.  McShane also said Dollar General is limited by necessary investments into infrastructure and its supply chain.
